description:
&lt;p&gt;FIXED TERM OPPORTUNITY UNTIL MARCH 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an opportunity for a talented individual to join our Wigan Administrative Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is vital in supporting our aim to provide exceptional patient care, every time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using your organisational, administration, communication and people skills, you will contribute towards an effective and consistent level of service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our patients and service users are at the heart of everything we do and we would like to hear from applicants who share this commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a must have, you will possess:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong administration skills including the ability to manage a diverse and busy workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent telephone manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and experience dealing with queries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to delivering outstanding customer service / patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sensitivity and empathy required when dealing with callers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Microsoft Office, Outlook and other IT systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to a standard Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check. Successful candidates will either have a valid DBS check with the Trust or will be required to pay for the cost of the DBS Disclosure which is £29.50, the cost of which will be deducted from first salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Buffey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Admin Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01942 636303&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;louise.buffey@nwbh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
